sundays with the st lawrence events at stanford sundays with the st lawrence facebook twitter email print add to calendar it's fair to say that the partnership between the st lawrence string quartet and osvaldo golijov has been among the deepest of collaborations and friendships for both an early champion of golijov's music the quartet earned two grammy nominations for its 2002 recording of his yiddishbbuk which they reprised for us with gusto last season golijov's new work commissioned by stanford lively arts will be paired with a major work by schubert one of golijov's favorite composers program osvaldo golijov new work schubert string quartet no 15 in g major d 887 1826 additional work tba sundays with the st lawrence is presented in partnership with music at stanford generously supported by paul and iris brest golijov commission generously supported by kathryn gould when sunday october 23 2011 2 30 pm where dinkelspiel auditorium map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students tags performance music arts sponsor department of music stanford lively arts contact 650 725 arts 2787 livelyarts stanford edu admission reserved seating $44 50 permalink http events stanford edu events 284 28459 more info last modified october 19 2011
